# SauceDemo Automation Test

This project contains automated tests for the Sauce Labs Sample Application (https://www.saucedemo.com/) using Selenium and TestNG.

## Table of Contents

- [Prerequisites](#prerequisites)
- [Installation](#installation)
- [Running the Tests](#running-the-tests)
- [Test Description](#test-description)
- [Project Structure](#project-structure)

## Prerequisites

Before you can run the tests, make sure you have the following software installed:

- [Java Development Kit (JDK)](https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/javase-downloads.html) (version 8 or higher)
- [Apache Maven](https://maven.apache.org/install.html)
- [Google Chrome](https://www.google.com/chrome/)

## Installation

1. **Clone the repository:**

   ```
   git clone https://github.com/Samzeeke/OfficeNg-Assesment.git
   cd saucedemo-automation-test


 2. Set up Maven:

Ensure Maven is installed and configured properly. You can verify the installation by running:
mvn -v

3. Install project dependencies:
mvn clean install

Running the Tests
To run the tests, use the following command:
mvn test

  
*This command will execute the SauceDemo test class and provide a test report in the console.*

Test Description
The SauceDemo test class performs the following steps:

-Navigate to the Sauce Labs Sample Application in Incognito mode.
-Enter valid credentials to log in.
-Verify that the login is successful and the user is redirected to the products page.
-Select a T-shirt by clicking on its image or name.
-Verify that the T-shirt details page is displayed.
-Click the "Add to Cart" button.
-Verify that the T-shirt is added to the cart successfully.
-Navigate to the cart by clicking the cart icon or accessing the cart page directly.
-Verify that the cart page is displayed.
-Review the items in the cart and ensure that the T-shirt is listed with the correct details (name, price, quantity, etc.).
-Click the "Checkout" button.
-Verify that the checkout information page is displayed.
-Enter the required checkout information (e.g., name, shipping address, payment details).
-Click the "Continue" button.
-Verify that the order summary page is displayed, showing the T-shirt details and the total amount.
-Click the "Finish" button.
-Verify that the order confirmation page is displayed, indicating a successful purchase.
-Logout from the application.
-Verify that the user is successfully logged out and redirected to the login page.


  *Project Structure*
saucedemo-automation-test
│
├── src
│   ├── main
│   │   └── java
│   │       └── org
│   │           └── example
│   │               └── SauceDemo.java
│   └── test
│       └── java
│           └── org
│               └── example
│                   └── SauceDemoTest.java
│
├── pom.xml
└── README.md

src/main/java/org/example/SauceDemo.java: Contains the main test logic for the Sauce Labs Sample Application.
src/test/java/org/example/SauceDemoTest.java: Test class for executing the tests.
pom.xml: Maven configuration file, which includes dependencies and build configuration.
README.md: This file containing project instructions.
Dependencies

The project uses the following main dependencies:

Selenium: Web browser automation.
TestNG: Testing framework.
WebDriverManager: Automatically manages browser drivers for Selenium.
You can find the exact versions and additional dependencies in the pom.xml file.
